    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Never use the PTO gear as a pressing base. The narrow width of this gear can cause breakage.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear retaining snap ring from each countershaft front (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300791">Figure 91</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300791" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300791" filename="../figg13/g1300791.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 91. Remove Drive Gear Retaining Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the rear face of the 4th speed gear as a base and press the drive gear, PTO gear, and
                4th speed gear from each countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300792">Figure 92</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300792" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300792" filename="../figg13/g1300792.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 92. Press Drive Gear, PTO Gear and 4th Speed Gear From Each Countershaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the rear face of 2nd speed gear as a base and press 3rd speed gear and 2nd speed gear
                from each countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300793">Figure 93</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300793" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300793" filename="../figg13/g1300793.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 93. Press 3rd and 2nd Speed Gear From Each Countershaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the keys; replace if necessary (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300794">Figure 94</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300794" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300794" filename="../figg13/g1300794.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 94. Inspect Keys</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
